- The integer array parameter `price` contains positive integers.
- The integer parameter `k` is a positive integer.
- The integer result is the maximum tastiness of a candy basket.
- The integer result is the smallest absolute difference of the prices of any two candies in the basket.
- The store sells baskets of `k` distinct candies.
- The maximum tastiness is achieved by choosing `k` candies with the smallest absolute price difference.